You’re uncertain what this adventure leads to...
...but you are in a state of mind, a time, and a place...
...where the unreal becomes real...
...the unknown becomes known...
...and what you assumed, did not exist...?
It has been there this whole time.

Like sleeping with a blade in hand, or drinking poison that could easily take your life, 
the uncanny valley is not child’s play.

When you think of this place, your awareness becomes heightened.
Your insecurities become your only defense...
...because this state of uncertainty, is all that is keeping you alive.

*pause*
Good. Hopefully that just woke your ass up. Time to land a rhetorical question...

What if, the things you take for granted, the things you wholly believe in, the things you’re not sure why you 
like, the things you have no other explanation for doing, other than... because everyone else does it too...?

What if, behind these things, this mask you trust, and this LIFE you lead...
